The paper focuses on the usage of web search in software engineering, which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also involves analyzing query logs and building a machine learning classifier, which falls under the subfield of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the taxonomy of intents behind the usage of web search, which relates to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the study on improving search engine support for developers, which could fall under the subfield of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
